description.narrative: A total of 73 health workers, including 61 women and 12 men, were trained in essential newborn care. The Mother Kangaroo Care service is operational at the Center of Excellence for Newborns at the National Reference Hospital Center in El Maarouf and allowed for caring for 133 premature newborns, as of September 30, 2019. Three centers of excellence and seven other health services are equipped with equipment, consumables and reagents for the management of newborn emergencies. A standard guide for quality neonatal care has been developed to serve as a reference in neonatal and maternity services in the country. | Status:Met | As-of Date:17/01/2020
